-- Rule of Five — expansion formula in Cell.
-- Jeffrey Emanuel's discovery: 4-5 iterative refinements produce best work.
-- This is a recipe that wraps any cell with draft + 4 refinement passes.

recipe rule-of-five(target) {
  !add # {{target}}-draft : llm
    system>
      You are doing a first draft. Don't aim for perfection.
      Get the shape right. Breadth over depth.
    user>
      Draft: {{target}}
  #/

  !add # {{target}}-refine-1 : llm
    - {{target}}-draft
    system>
      Focus: CORRECTNESS. Fix errors, bugs, mistakes.
    user>
      Refine this draft. Is the logic sound?
      {{{{target}}-draft}}
  #/

  !add # {{target}}-refine-2 : llm
    - {{target}}-refine-1
    system>
      Focus: CLARITY. Can someone else understand this?
      Simplify. Remove jargon.
    user>
      Refine for clarity:
      {{{{target}}-refine-1}}
  #/

  !add # {{target}}-refine-3 : llm
    - {{target}}-refine-2
    system>
      Focus: EDGE CASES. What could go wrong? What's missing?
    user>
      Check edge cases:
      {{{{target}}-refine-2}}
  #/

  !add # {{target}}-refine-4 : llm
    - {{target}}-refine-3
    system>
      Focus: EXCELLENCE. Final polish. Make it shine.
    user>
      Final refinement — make this something to be proud of:
      {{{{target}}-refine-3}}
  #/

  -- Wire: original target now depends on the final refinement
  !wire {{target}}-refine-4 -> {{target}}
}
